The Helios Airways flight ZU522 crashed near Athens, sparking anger among relatives at Larnaca airport.
Reports of past decompression issues fueled suspicions of a technical fault.
Experts suggested that a loss of cabin pressure could have led to the tragedy.
Fighter jets shadowed the plane, revealing an unconscious co-pilot and no captain in the cockpit.
Despite efforts to regain control, the Boeing 737 ultimately crashed into a mountainside.
The cause of the crash, which claimed 121 lives, was attributed to a technical problem.
Condolences were expressed by EU officials to the victims' families.
